
                                            Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane released the findings of her investigation on Monday, which found the Eastern Cape government had not planned for the funeral.
 
                                         CAPE TOWN - The Eastern Cape government says it is still studying the Public Protector's report which found hundreds of millions of rands meant for former president Nelson Mandela's funeral  were misappropriated. Busisiwe Mkhwebane released the findings of her investigation on Monday, which found the Eastern Cape government had not planned for the funeral. Provincial government spokesperson Sonwabo Mbananga says they're still studying the report. “To understand what is contained in the report, including the recommended remedial action. Once we have satisfied ourselves as to the content of this report we will then be able to offer a much more comprehensive and substantial report as the provincial government.” Mbananga adds the province is against corruption, especially in public service. “We maintain a zero-tolerance stance against any acts that constitute corruption, maladministration and the improver handling of public funds.”